                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="1006" type="ms"/>
                        <dateline>1847— Saturday 4. Dec<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi></dateline>
                        <list>
                            <item>Muzzey.</item>
                            <item>Howard John</item>
                            <item>Mitchell John</item>
                            <item>Abbot Amos</item>
                            <item>Giddings Joshua R.</item>
                            <item>Williams Otho H.</item>
                            <item>Kavasales.</item>
                            <item>Hall N. K.</item>
                            <item>Russell</item>
                            <item>Hudson Charles</item>
                            <item>Seaton W. W</item>
                            <item>Whittlesey Elisha</item>
                            <item>Brent William</item>
                       
                            <item>Fendall Philip R.</item> </list>
                        <p>A multitude of visitors</p>
                        <p>Some Members of Congress others candidates for offices to be elected at
                            the organization of Congress and especially of the house of
                            Representatives next Monday— I went to the </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1847-12-05">
                    <head>5 December 1847</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1847-12-05"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="1007" type="ms"/>
                        <dateline>1847— Sunday 5. Dec<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi></dateline>
                        <p>Heard Bishop Hughes preach this morning in the Clerk’s seat of H.R.U.S.
                            in very plain episcopal robes,—he repeated from the Mass Book in English
                            a general prayer of blessing upon all mankind, and upon men of all
                            conditions—</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
