                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1847-12-24">
                    <head>24 December 1847</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1847-12-24"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor>
                        <subject>Health and Illness</subject>
                    </bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="1017" type="ms"/>
                        <dateline>1847. Friday 24. December</dateline>
                        <p>Visits to <persRef ref="davis-john4">John Davis</persRef> Senator from
                            Massachusetts at <persRef ref="willard-henry">Willard’s</persRef> City
                            Hotel— He is so ill that he cannot see visitors but better than he was—
                            At the Post Office of H.R— Directory not yet ready— Call on <persRef
                                ref="giddings-joshua">Giddings</persRef> at <persRef ref="sprig-b"
                                    >M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Spriggs</persRef>—on <persRef ref="greene-albert">M<hi
                                        rend="superscript">r</hi> Greene</persRef> Senator from R. Island and <persRef ref="hannegan-edward">Hannegan</persRef>
                            Senator from Indiana neither of them at his lodgings— Left cards— Walk
                            home with <persRef ref="robinson-john6">Robinson</persRef>.— <persRef ref="thomas-john7">Thomas D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> John M</persRef> here—
                            Medical visit—</p>

                        <pb n="1019" type="ms"/>
                        <lg>
                            <l>Muse! couldst thou see with microscopic eye</l>
                            <l>The Souls of all the men assembled here</l>
                            <l>With penetration keen couldst thou descry</l>
                            <l>The secret source of each one’s hope or fear</l>
                            <l>With vision from above if thou couldst pry</l>
                            <l>And trace the latent spring of souls or tear </l>
                            <l>Would not thy book comprize within its plan</l>
                            <l>In living light the history of Man?</l>
                            <l>Fair Muse of History! to Fancy’s ken</l>
                            <l>Thou <unclear>and thy</unclear> Car with Time keepst even pace</l>
                            <l>And day by day with thy recording pen</l>
                            <l>Dost mark the <unclear>annals</unclear> of the pilgrim race</l>
                        </lg>
                    </div>
